======================================================================
  SECTION 5: Fifth Power Sum Identity
======================================================================

For S = QR_p, λ_k = (χ(k)·g - 1)/2 where g = g(χ).
So λ_k^5 = (1/32)(χ(k)g - 1)^5

Expanding (χ(k)g - 1)^5 by binomial theorem:
  = Σ_{j=0}^{5} C(5,j) (χ(k)g)^j (-1)^{5-j}
  = -1 + 5χg - 10g² + 10χg³ - 5g⁴ + χg⁵
  (using χ(k)^j = χ(k) for odd j, 1 for even j, when k≠0)

p= 5: g²=5.00-0.00j (expect χ(-1)·p = 5), c_5(Paley)=2, formula check: 2.26e-14
p= 7: g²=-7.00+0.00j (expect χ(-1)·p = -7), c_5(Paley)=42, formula check: 8.99e-14
p=11: g²=-11.00+0.00j (expect χ(-1)·p = -11), c_5(Paley)=594, formula check: 5.67e-13
p=13: g²=13.00-0.00j (expect χ(-1)·p = 13), c_5(Paley)=1482, formula check: 2.73e-12
p=17: g²=17.00+0.00j (expect χ(-1)·p = 17), c_5(Paley)=6392, formula check: 3.64e-12
p=19: g²=-19.00+0.00j (expect χ(-1)·p = -19), c_5(Paley)=11628, formula check: 8.10e-12
p=23: g²=-23.00+0.00j (expect χ(-1)·p = -23), c_5(Paley)=31878, formula check: 3.20e-11

======================================================================
  SECTION 6: Closed Form for c_5(Paley_p)
======================================================================

Using g² = χ(-1)·p:
  For p ≡ 3 mod 4: g² = -p, g⁴ = p²
  For p ≡ 1 mod 4: g² = p,  g⁴ = p²

Σ_{k≠0} λ_k^5 = (p-1)/32 · (-1 - 10·χ(-1)·p - 5p²)

Total: 5·c_5 = ((p-1)/2)^5 + (p-1)/32·(-1 - 10·χ(-1)·p - 5p²)

  p= 5: χ(-1)=+1, c_5 =        2, direct=       2  ✓
  p= 7: χ(-1)=-1, c_5 =       42, direct=      42  ✓
  p=11: χ(-1)=-1, c_5 =      594, direct=     594  ✓
  p=13: χ(-1)=+1, c_5 =     1482, direct=    1482  ✓
  p=17: χ(-1)=+1, c_5 =     6392, direct=    6392  ✓
  p=19: χ(-1)=-1, c_5 =    11628, direct=   11628  ✓
  p=23: χ(-1)=-1, c_5 =    31878, direct=   31878  ✓
  p=29: χ(-1)=+1, c_5 =   106778, direct=  106778  ✓
  p=31: χ(-1)=-1, c_5 =   151032, direct=  151032  ✓

======================================================================
  SECTION 6b: Simplified c_5(Paley_p) Formula
======================================================================

5·c_5(Paley_p) = ((p-1)/2)^5 + (p-1)/32 · (-1 - 10χ(-1)p - 5p²)

Let's separate by residue class of p mod 4:

Case p ≡ 1 (mod 4):  χ(-1) = +1
  5c_5 = (p-1)^5/32 + (p-1)(-1 - 10p - 5p²)/32
       = (p-1)/32 · [(p-1)^4 - 1 - 10p - 5p²]

Case p ≡ 3 (mod 4):  χ(-1) = -1
  5c_5 = (p-1)^5/32 + (p-1)(-1 + 10p - 5p²)/32
       = (p-1)/32 · [(p-1)^4 - 1 + 10p - 5p²]

Expanding (p-1)^4 = p^4 - 4p^3 + 6p^2 - 4p + 1:

Case p ≡ 1 (mod 4):
  bracket = p^4 - 4p^3 + 6p^2 - 4p + 1 - 1 - 10p - 5p^2
         = p^4 - 4p^3 + p^2 - 14p
         = p(p^3 - 4p^2 + p - 14)

Case p ≡ 3 (mod 4):
  bracket = p^4 - 4p^3 + 6p^2 - 4p + 1 - 1 + 10p - 5p^2
         = p^4 - 4p^3 + p^2 + 6p
         = p(p^3 - 4p^2 + p + 6)

So: 5c_5(Paley_p) = p(p-1)/32 × f(p)
  where f(p) = p³ - 4p² + p - 14  if p ≡ 1 (mod 4)
        f(p) = p³ - 4p² + p + 6   if p ≡ 3 (mod 4)

  p= 5 ≡ 1 mod 4: f(p)=    16, c_5 =        2, direct =        2  ✓
  p= 7 ≡ 3 mod 4: f(p)=   160, c_5 =       42, direct =       42  ✓
  p=11 ≡ 3 mod 4: f(p)=   864, c_5 =      594, direct =      594  ✓
  p=13 ≡ 1 mod 4: f(p)=  1520, c_5 =     1482, direct =     1482  ✓
  p=17 ≡ 1 mod 4: f(p)=  3760, c_5 =     6392, direct =     6392  ✓
  p=19 ≡ 3 mod 4: f(p)=  5440, c_5 =    11628, direct =    11628  ✓
  p=23 ≡ 3 mod 4: f(p)= 10080, c_5 =    31878, direct =    31878  ✓
  p=29 ≡ 1 mod 4: f(p)= 21040, c_5 =   106778, direct =   106778  ✓
  p=31 ≡ 3 mod 4: f(p)= 25984, c_5 =   151032, direct =   151032  ✓

